1
00:00:00,117 --> 00:00:01,404
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,407 --> 00:00:02,965
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,694 --> 00:00:05,820
He gave us jewelry as a dying apology.

4
00:00:06,130 --> 00:00:07,948
Is that really so unbearable to you?

5
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:09,945
What? Theft?

6
00:00:10,604 --> 00:00:11,641
Do it.

7
00:00:11,643 --> 00:00:13,100
Go ahead.

8
00:00:13,113 --> 00:00:16,501
- Let's see who people blame.
- Fine, go ahead.

9
00:00:16,503 --> 00:00:18,422
You think I won't?

10
00:00:18,994 --> 00:00:21,745
So you're finally showing your true face.

11
00:00:21,859 --> 00:00:24,128
Acting all kind and innocent,

12
00:00:24,130 --> 00:00:27,368
while smiling like that
and driving people to ruin.

13
00:00:27,370 --> 00:00:29,592
I wonder if the world knows.

14
00:00:29,751 --> 00:00:33,179
It's all because of you that he got sick!

15
00:00:33,382 --> 00:00:37,135
- Get out. Do you want to be dragged out?
- Kill me!

16
00:00:37,137 --> 00:00:41,189
I'm not leaving until I get my money back.

17
00:00:41,191 --> 00:00:44,029
That jewelry was bought with my money!

18
00:00:44,031 --> 00:00:46,149
It was paid for with our joint card!

19
00:00:46,761 --> 00:00:48,667
How will you prove
you were legally married?

20
00:00:49,154 --> 00:00:51,689
You don't even have a single document,
yet you emptied the account.

21
00:00:52,035 --> 00:00:54,562
You must've stood at the ATM
for hours withdrawing it all.

22
00:00:55,535 --> 00:00:57,331
That must've felt pretty pathetic
and miserable.

23
00:00:57,904 --> 00:00:58,904
You...

24
00:01:03,244 --> 00:01:04,378
Go.

25
00:01:05,494 --> 00:01:06,940
Let's stop this, both of us.

26
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,991
I can't give you what he wanted
to give the kids.

27
00:01:11,877 --> 00:01:13,733
But I'll return what he wanted to give me.

28
00:01:14,772 --> 00:01:15,860
Take it and leave.

29
00:01:19,861 --> 00:01:20,889
Mom.

30
00:01:21,335 --> 00:01:24,532
No. You can't. Don't give it to her.

31
00:01:26,739 --> 00:01:30,852
I even gave her my husband.
What does this jewelry matter?

32
00:01:45,637 --> 00:01:46,648
Mom.

33
00:01:47,291 --> 00:01:48,758
Mom, are you okay?

34
00:01:50,421 --> 00:01:51,824
Why are you here?

35
00:01:52,756 --> 00:01:54,501
Why do you think?

36
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:59,554
Why did you come all the way here again?

37
00:02:00,499 --> 00:02:01,811
Isn't it all over?

38
00:02:01,813 --> 00:02:05,381
I just got back from taking care of
your wedding jewelry.

39
00:02:05,676 --> 00:02:07,613
You must feel so lucky.

40
00:02:13,270 --> 00:02:14,286
What do you mean?

41
00:02:14,288 --> 00:02:16,115
Go in and ask her.

42
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:20,774
She treats us like dirt.
I never thought she'd do this.

43
00:02:22,005 --> 00:02:24,516
You finally learned how to talk back.

44
00:02:33,997 --> 00:02:35,749
I'll never forgive him.

45
00:02:35,856 --> 00:02:38,440
I'll never forgive him!

46
00:02:39,013 --> 00:02:43,663
That bastard,
how could he betray me like this?

47
00:02:43,665 --> 00:02:48,732
How could he do this to me?

48
00:02:49,546 --> 00:02:55,086
Mom, stop! Enough!

49
00:02:55,088 --> 00:02:59,545
It's not fair! I'm so angry!

50
00:03:01,361 --> 00:03:03,617
I'm so angry.

51
00:03:03,619 --> 00:03:05,421
Mom!

52
00:03:06,090 --> 00:03:09,653
Mom!

53
00:03:12,546 --> 00:03:15,631
You're saying that man bought this
for my wedding?

54
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:17,403
I was the one who picked them out.

55
00:03:17,704 --> 00:03:20,760
She returned everything except this
and O Reum's first birthday ring.

56
00:03:20,762 --> 00:03:22,413
Then why did she return hers?

57
00:03:22,415 --> 00:03:24,001
Exactly.

58
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:27,145
She was vicious earlier.

59
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:33,257
I wish we could just take that house too.

60
00:03:33,426 --> 00:03:34,426
"The house?"

61
00:03:34,610 --> 00:03:36,057
I told you not to.

62
00:03:38,392 --> 00:03:39,465
Let's...

63
00:03:39,884 --> 00:03:43,676
sell this house and use our share
of the other property to move to Gangnam.

64
00:03:43,678 --> 00:03:45,980
Dad told me to check
the company shares too.

65
00:03:45,982 --> 00:03:48,118
Why would you even bring something
like that up to your father?

66
00:03:48,336 --> 00:03:50,727
You keep this up
and mom's seriously going to chew you out.

67
00:03:51,339 --> 00:03:56,986
The other side broke the rules first.
We're just taking what's rightfully ours.

68
00:03:58,311 --> 00:04:00,502
Do I look like I'm being greedy?

69
00:04:02,522 --> 00:04:05,364
I'm doing this for O Reum,

70
00:04:05,939 --> 00:04:09,230
so I'm never backing down,
you hopeless brothers.

71
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:18,453
Figures. A real Joan of Arc.

72
00:04:18,837 --> 00:04:21,818
Since she didn't say it was for me,

73
00:04:22,115 --> 00:04:24,038
I'll stay out of it.

74
00:04:47,336 --> 00:04:49,179
Yeong Ju,
I heard you had quite a confrontation.

75
00:04:49,466 --> 00:04:53,725
When you lose your temper, it's scary.
She must've been shocked.

76
00:04:54,956 --> 00:04:56,917
I don't even know what I'm doing anymore.

77
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:04,576
Give this back too.

78
00:05:04,793 --> 00:05:08,358
I don't want to get married wearing
jewelry that man bought. It's bad luck.

79
00:05:08,908 --> 00:05:12,997
But I do want you
to keep everything that's yours.

80
00:05:12,999 --> 00:05:15,292
Don't start this again. It's over.

81
00:05:16,463 --> 00:05:20,633
By the way, do you actually have someone?

82
00:05:21,861 --> 00:05:24,237
You always said it was just me,
so you were lying?

83
00:05:24,764 --> 00:05:27,695
Of course you're number one.

84
00:05:28,059 --> 00:05:31,584
There is a woman I love
just a little less than you.

85
00:05:31,947 --> 00:05:33,137
I'll introduce you.

86
00:05:33,865 --> 00:05:35,237
What's she like?

87
00:05:35,923 --> 00:05:39,946
She's a writer. Kind, pretty,

88
00:05:40,686 --> 00:05:42,706
- and not an affair.
- Of course not.

89
00:05:43,298 --> 00:05:44,668
You really have to say it like that?

90
00:05:49,924 --> 00:05:50,924
You okay?

91
00:05:51,672 --> 00:05:52,969
Feels good, right?

92
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:54,705
Smart eldest daughter-in-law,

93
00:05:54,707 --> 00:05:59,347
kind and pretty second one,
you've got it all.

94
00:06:00,466 --> 00:06:01,826
You're such a smooth talker.

95
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:06,309
Just sleep. Don't think about anything.

96
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:09,932
You smell like cigarettes.

97
00:06:09,934 --> 00:06:11,961
When are you going to quit?

98
00:06:13,722 --> 00:06:15,199
Got caught.

99
00:06:16,521 --> 00:06:18,599
Good night, Yeong Ju.

100
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,831
Nice, right?

101
00:06:36,061 --> 00:06:38,134
I don't really like fishing,
but today feels nice.

102
00:06:42,422 --> 00:06:43,478
- Joong Bin.
- Yes?

103
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:46,395
- Am I tone-deaf? Did that sound weird?
- No.

104
00:06:46,644 --> 00:06:47,719
It sounded good.

105
00:06:58,562 --> 00:06:59,751
General!

106
00:07:00,724 --> 00:07:02,438
Lieutenant No, you're here.

107
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:03,717
Got everything for the spicy fish stew?

108
00:07:03,719 --> 00:07:06,801
Yes, I should've prepared in advance.
Sorry about that.

109
00:07:06,803 --> 00:07:09,425
By the way, were you two singing?

110
00:07:09,427 --> 00:07:11,275
Why? Was it bad?

111
00:07:11,277 --> 00:07:14,740
- No.
- My brother and I have good voices.

112
00:07:15,559 --> 00:07:17,584
What song was that? It sounds familiar.

113
00:07:17,587 --> 00:07:20,043
This? It's Schubert's "Die Forelle."

114
00:07:21,465 --> 00:07:24,778
I see. Nice arrangement, too.

115
00:07:24,780 --> 00:07:25,921
This?

116
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:34,578
Hello? Just a second.

117
00:07:34,990 --> 00:07:37,994
- Hey.
- Yes.

118
00:07:39,909 --> 00:07:42,082
It's a woman. Right?

119
00:07:42,476 --> 00:07:44,512
He wouldn't let just anyone
hold his fishing rod.

120
00:07:44,514 --> 00:07:47,311
Exactly. It has to be a woman.

121
00:07:47,803 --> 00:07:51,548
- An attorney?
- Yeah, an inheritance attorney.

122
00:07:51,550 --> 00:07:55,508
I'm especially curious about inheritance
in common-law marriages.

123
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:57,963
You've probably noticed...

124
00:07:57,966 --> 00:08:00,701
that you're the only one
I can comfortably talk to about this now.

125
00:08:01,896 --> 00:08:04,929
Okay, thank you.

126
00:08:12,308 --> 00:08:15,149
I really hate you.

127
00:08:15,861 --> 00:08:19,170
If you keep this up,
your precious Ji Ni...

128
00:08:19,172 --> 00:08:21,143
will end up with nothing.

129
00:08:23,306 --> 00:08:24,506
(My Daughter, Ji Ni)

130
00:08:26,852 --> 00:08:27,852
Yes.

131
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:30,151
Mom, did you eat lunch?

132
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:32,530
Don't just stay in bed. Make sure you eat.

133
00:08:32,532 --> 00:08:35,394
Who do you think I am? You worry too much.

134
00:08:35,638 --> 00:08:37,871
You should eat well too. Don't get weak.

135
00:08:38,008 --> 00:08:39,814
Did you take your herbal tonic pills?

136
00:08:40,472 --> 00:08:43,057
Okay. Bye.

137
00:08:56,025 --> 00:08:57,248
Yes, sir.

138
00:08:59,999 --> 00:09:01,846
Yes, I'm fine now.

139
00:09:02,337 --> 00:09:05,197
Thank you for coming by
despite your busy schedule.

140
00:09:05,866 --> 00:09:08,113
I'll return to work next week.

141
00:09:09,465 --> 00:09:10,465
Tomorrow?

142
00:09:11,274 --> 00:09:13,676
Yes, I understand.

143
00:09:14,373 --> 00:09:15,373
Bye.

144
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:22,646
I'm starting next week.
Why does he want to see me?

145
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,813
Our organization is conservative.

146
00:09:26,815 --> 00:09:29,003
It's a national orchestra too.

147
00:09:34,273 --> 00:09:36,468
It's a minefield.

148
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:40,906
Mom. Honey.

149
00:09:41,839 --> 00:09:43,535
I need your help.

150
00:09:49,544 --> 00:09:50,848
Come here.

151
00:09:55,421 --> 00:09:56,463
Keep quiet.

152
00:09:57,314 --> 00:09:58,948
Hold this for me.

153
00:10:08,073 --> 00:10:09,249
Are you okay?

154
00:10:25,452 --> 00:10:27,441
Stop hitting him!

155
00:10:40,068 --> 00:10:41,921
Why are you doing this to him?

156
00:10:42,474 --> 00:10:43,943
Who are you?

157
00:10:55,317 --> 00:10:57,488
She can't risk hurting her hand like this.

158
00:10:57,490 --> 00:11:00,373
She got hurt because of you.
Is that how you thank her?

159
00:11:00,375 --> 00:11:03,285
Did I ask her to save me? How ridiculous.

160
00:11:03,984 --> 00:11:05,544
Let's go.

161
00:11:14,284 --> 00:11:17,669
Wasn't that Na Ji Ni? That was amazing.

162
00:11:17,671 --> 00:11:19,751
So she really did bully someone.

163
00:11:20,616 --> 00:11:22,538
How is saving someone bullying?

164
00:12:00,716 --> 00:12:05,052
Why did you save me? I told you not to.

165
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,043
I don't want to live.

166
00:12:09,456 --> 00:12:11,295
Don't touch me!

167
00:12:12,611 --> 00:12:14,456
I said, don't touch me!

168
00:12:21,525 --> 00:12:22,695
Director.

169
00:12:22,697 --> 00:12:25,760
I heard your girlfriend is an artist too.
Why didn't she come with you?

170
00:12:25,762 --> 00:12:27,700
We would've liked to meet her.

171
00:12:27,703 --> 00:12:29,605
She's busy preparing for her exhibition.

172
00:12:30,448 --> 00:12:32,969
And she's probably seen
a lot of work like this in Europe.

173
00:12:32,971 --> 00:12:34,238
I suppose so.

174
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:37,659
- Please invite us to her exhibition.
- Of course.

175
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:44,612
Excuse me.

176
00:12:54,904 --> 00:12:56,510
(Ji Hu's mother)

177
00:12:57,446 --> 00:12:58,789
Yes, Mother.

178
00:12:59,222 --> 00:13:00,235
Now?

179
00:13:00,969 --> 00:13:03,931
I'm at the studio,
preparing for my exhibition.

180
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:05,322
You know that.

181
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:06,961
Yes, Mother.

182
00:13:07,978 --> 00:13:10,746
You'll have to go alone. Yes.

183
00:13:11,214 --> 00:13:13,658
Yes, I understand.

184
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:24,473
Just finish the handover
instead of nagging me!

185
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:33,005
Put this on first.

186
00:13:35,751 --> 00:13:37,839
If it gets infected,
it'll take a long time to heal.

187
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:41,398
An artist shouldn't be
careless with her hands.

188
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,557
Why are you doing this?

189
00:13:44,134 --> 00:13:46,265
Are we close enough
to check on each other?

190
00:13:49,864 --> 00:13:53,719
Sometimes you're scary,
sometimes like a child,

191
00:13:54,225 --> 00:13:55,795
and sometimes like a professional.

192
00:13:57,652 --> 00:13:59,863
When did you learn to fight like that?

193
00:14:14,815 --> 00:14:16,523
This looks like your painting.

194
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:19,648
I can see how it comforts people.

195
00:14:20,898 --> 00:14:22,586
You think it comforts people?

196
00:14:22,981 --> 00:14:24,065
I think so.

197
00:14:25,058 --> 00:14:27,023
How could I do this job if I couldn't?

198
00:14:32,983 --> 00:14:34,326
Just hurry up and finish this.

199
00:14:35,025 --> 00:14:38,393
As someone who manages artists,
I can't stop worrying about your hand.

200
00:14:48,190 --> 00:14:49,597
Are you filling the vacant spot?

201
00:14:55,023 --> 00:14:57,898
A spot opened up on the new artist team
after the international student left.

202
00:14:58,474 --> 00:15:00,849
Ms. Na wasn't rejected
because of her work.

203
00:15:01,843 --> 00:15:03,604
Until we know exactly what happened,

204
00:15:03,606 --> 00:15:04,981
she can't enter any competitions.

205
00:15:05,023 --> 00:15:06,231
Director,

206
00:15:06,356 --> 00:15:08,863
I looked into her background.

207
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:09,893
You did?

208
00:15:09,896 --> 00:15:12,688
She was known for her beauty and talent
at Cheongrok School.

209
00:15:12,690 --> 00:15:14,190
But, as you know,

210
00:15:14,231 --> 00:15:16,523
She dropped out after getting caught up
in a school bullying case.

211
00:15:16,526 --> 00:15:19,688
Well, middle school is compulsory,
so she didn't technically drop out.

212
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,398
She graduated with minimal attendance.

213
00:15:22,283 --> 00:15:24,190
She never went to high school,

214
00:15:24,231 --> 00:15:25,938
and got into college with a GED.

215
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:27,609
She definitely has talent.

216
00:15:28,293 --> 00:15:29,981
It was serious enough to convene...

217
00:15:30,023 --> 00:15:31,773
a school violence committee.

218
00:15:34,090 --> 00:15:35,430
Could she be a female Dr. Jekyll?

219
00:15:35,443 --> 00:15:36,472
"Dr. Jekyll?"

220
00:15:36,996 --> 00:15:38,440
Her paintings and her personality...

221
00:15:38,481 --> 00:15:40,938
don't match at all, like Dr. Jekyll.

222
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,322
That's a little harsh.

223
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:44,798
Are you done looking? Shall we go?

224
00:15:45,181 --> 00:15:47,315
Dinner's on me. Chicken and beer.

225
00:15:47,356 --> 00:15:50,000
Perfect. Nothing beats chicken and beer
on a summer night.

226
00:15:50,349 --> 00:15:51,386
Let's go.

227
00:16:08,898 --> 00:16:10,604
I'm sorry to bring this up...

228
00:16:10,606 --> 00:16:12,256
when you've been through so much,

229
00:16:13,231 --> 00:16:15,354
but if you resign...

230
00:16:15,356 --> 00:16:17,315
for personal reasons,

231
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:20,315
we'll make sure it looks favorable
on our end.

232
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,981
Are my performances not good enough?

233
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,184
Se Ri,

234
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:28,484
Korean society is a conservative one.

235
00:16:29,023 --> 00:16:31,624
We'll take you off the roster
starting with the upcoming concert.

236
00:16:35,231 --> 00:16:36,440
Sir,

237
00:16:37,247 --> 00:16:38,788
please help me.

238
00:16:39,065 --> 00:16:41,273
Performing is my life.

239
00:16:41,339 --> 00:16:43,214
There's nothing I can do to help.

240
00:16:43,606 --> 00:16:44,815
I'm sorry.

241
00:17:02,612 --> 00:17:03,820
It's okay.

242
00:17:04,525 --> 00:17:05,816
My talent won't disappear.

243
00:17:07,198 --> 00:17:08,406
I can hold a solo recital.

244
00:17:09,538 --> 00:17:11,056
I can show them what I can do.

245
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:51,106
Sa Bin.

246
00:17:51,148 --> 00:17:53,690
I just heard from my lawyer friend.

247
00:17:53,815 --> 00:17:55,316
It's not good news.

248
00:17:56,182 --> 00:17:58,266
His legal wife must recognize your claim.

249
00:17:59,057 --> 00:18:00,938
Try asking her to acknowledge...

250
00:18:00,940 --> 00:18:03,440
that you helped build his wealth.

251
00:18:03,648 --> 00:18:05,731
Otherwise, we'll have to file a lawsuit.

252
00:18:07,315 --> 00:18:09,938
Legally,
the legal wife has the advantage...

253
00:18:09,940 --> 00:18:11,106
in principle.

254
00:18:14,065 --> 00:18:15,273
Hello?

255
00:18:16,949 --> 00:18:18,788
Yes, I understand.

256
00:18:20,148 --> 00:18:21,615
Thank you for looking into it.

257
00:18:22,996 --> 00:18:24,896
You don't sound well.

258
00:18:24,898 --> 00:18:27,398
Think about it later. Get some rest today.

259
00:18:28,606 --> 00:18:31,356
I will. Okay.

260
00:18:59,190 --> 00:19:00,773
Seriously.

261
00:19:03,773 --> 00:19:04,940
Here you go.

262
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,690
I'm so annoyed.

263
00:19:07,981 --> 00:19:09,188
What did you eat for lunch?

264
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,383
The usual stuff you eat at reunions.

265
00:19:11,398 --> 00:19:13,059
I've never been to a reunion.

266
00:19:13,859 --> 00:19:17,569
Those girls really knew
how to get under my skin.

267
00:19:18,026 --> 00:19:19,188
I'm so annoyed.

268
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:22,853
How dare they get under your skin
when you fund the whole reunion?

269
00:19:22,856 --> 00:19:24,478
Exactly.

270
00:19:24,481 --> 00:19:26,606
- I'm home.
- Look how red it is.

271
00:19:28,231 --> 00:19:29,320
Mom.

272
00:19:29,322 --> 00:19:33,231
Something she ate at the reunion
must've caused an allergic reaction.

273
00:19:33,273 --> 00:19:36,533
- What about medicine?
- I took some, but it's not going down.

274
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:41,148
Son, did you have dinner?

275
00:19:41,387 --> 00:19:44,604
People have always been jealous of you,

276
00:19:44,606 --> 00:19:46,673
but you're too trusting, ma'am.

277
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:48,815
You let them get to you every time.

278
00:19:50,065 --> 00:19:51,273
It stings.

279
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,706
This looks serious.

280
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:55,408
- We should go to the hospital.
- It's spread to her back too.

281
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,830
We can't wait. Let's go, Mom.

282
00:20:01,626 --> 00:20:02,835
This is so annoying.

283
00:20:03,732 --> 00:20:04,856
Please call dad.

284
00:20:04,892 --> 00:20:06,148
Okay, don't worry.

285
00:20:07,856 --> 00:20:09,565
It stings.

286
00:20:17,031 --> 00:20:18,364
Your coffee is ready.

287
00:20:24,655 --> 00:20:26,318
What? What's wrong?

288
00:20:26,898 --> 00:20:29,063
I feel like I know her,
but I don't know who she is.

289
00:20:29,065 --> 00:20:30,273
What are you talking about?

290
00:20:31,315 --> 00:20:33,520
I know her, but I don't know who she is.

291
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:35,853
Think carefully.

292
00:20:45,690 --> 00:20:46,898
Welcome.

293
00:20:51,231 --> 00:20:52,231
You're here?

294
00:20:52,648 --> 00:20:54,815
Hold on, I just need to send this.

295
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:56,898
Take your time.

296
00:20:59,106 --> 00:21:00,648
I'll take your order.

297
00:21:01,856 --> 00:21:03,648
One iced Americano, please.

298
00:21:03,731 --> 00:21:05,356
One iced Americano.

299
00:21:05,449 --> 00:21:07,177
I'll process your payment.

300
00:21:07,356 --> 00:21:08,565
Who is she?

301
00:21:09,606 --> 00:21:10,815
Who is she?

302
00:21:21,773 --> 00:21:23,952
I'm done.

303
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:25,940
The coffee.

304
00:21:30,481 --> 00:21:31,943
Your coffee is ready.

305
00:21:36,228 --> 00:21:38,238
That girl keeps looking at you.

306
00:21:38,882 --> 00:21:40,048
Do you know her?

307
00:21:40,231 --> 00:21:41,319
No.

308
00:21:42,437 --> 00:21:44,187
How about a musical tonight?

309
00:21:44,190 --> 00:21:45,398
Suddenly?

310
00:21:50,894 --> 00:21:52,370
You wanted to see this.

311
00:21:53,875 --> 00:21:55,780
I love it.

312
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:57,433
You've been going home early lately,

313
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,766
in full homebody mode,

314
00:21:58,773 --> 00:22:00,195
so I pulled some strings.

315
00:22:00,731 --> 00:22:02,747
My mother wasn't feeling well.

316
00:22:03,690 --> 00:22:06,523
Let's go. We should eat first,
then head to the theater.

317
00:22:06,681 --> 00:22:07,690
I'll treat you.

318
00:22:08,641 --> 00:22:09,739
Okay.

319
00:22:17,127 --> 00:22:18,635
Thank you. Goodbye.

320
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,463
Jung A.

321
00:22:32,523 --> 00:22:35,148
- It's her, right? You know?
- Know what?

322
00:22:35,190 --> 00:22:36,648
That upperclassman, Han Jeong Won.

323
00:22:36,731 --> 00:22:38,481
I was racking my brain trying to remember.

324
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,176
I knew her,
but I just couldn't recall her name.

325
00:22:40,848 --> 00:22:42,650
But the moment I heard her voice...

326
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:44,318
Eureka!

327
00:22:45,132 --> 00:22:46,882
Guess my memory's still working.

328
00:22:46,885 --> 00:22:48,201
Han Jeong Won?

329
00:22:49,715 --> 00:22:50,852
I don't know her.

330
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,368
You really make me work for it.

331
00:22:53,731 --> 00:22:55,881
Don't you know our department's queen
of juggling multiple guys?

332
00:22:56,231 --> 00:22:58,526
She dated multiple guys at once.
They even fought over her.

333
00:22:58,606 --> 00:23:00,395
She was kind of legendary.

334
00:23:00,398 --> 00:23:02,129
I don't know her...

335
00:23:03,044 --> 00:23:04,252
but I know the guy.

336
00:23:04,595 --> 00:23:06,229
Is she the type who plays guys?

337
00:23:07,182 --> 00:23:09,266
- Then what about that guy?
- He's the one getting played.

338
00:23:10,002 --> 00:23:11,585
I just looked her up.

339
00:23:11,606 --> 00:23:12,815
She's married.

340
00:23:13,026 --> 00:23:14,795
No wonder her account's private.

341
00:23:15,681 --> 00:23:17,188
I checked through a few connections.

342
00:23:17,190 --> 00:23:19,442
See? That guy isn't her husband.

343
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:22,043
- It's an affair.
- An affair?

344
00:23:22,907 --> 00:23:24,179
Then what about...

345
00:23:25,856 --> 00:23:27,479
What about that guy?

346
00:23:27,481 --> 00:23:29,916
He'll get dropped, just like the others.

347
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:33,478
Why? Do you know him well?

348
00:23:34,231 --> 00:23:36,249
He's good-looking.

349
00:23:36,599 --> 00:23:38,328
Tell him she's married.

350
00:23:38,343 --> 00:23:41,344
Tell him to be careful
before he gets sued for the affair.

351
00:23:41,766 --> 00:23:43,717
I heard she married into
a prominent family.

352
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:44,955
An affair?

353
00:23:46,106 --> 00:23:47,270
A lawsuit?

354
00:23:50,481 --> 00:23:51,690
Hold on.

355
00:23:54,315 --> 00:23:55,437
Mom.

356
00:23:56,324 --> 00:23:57,598
What's wrong with your voice?

357
00:23:59,277 --> 00:24:00,570
Okay, I'm coming right away.

358
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:03,018
Mom's sick. I have to go.

359
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,523
Okay. Go.

360
00:24:09,631 --> 00:24:11,316
Right on cue, she's sick again.

361
00:24:29,148 --> 00:24:30,356
Ji Ni.

362
00:24:32,940 --> 00:24:34,106
Ji Ni.

363
00:24:34,981 --> 00:24:36,190
Ji Ni.

364
00:24:38,565 --> 00:24:40,624
Mom, let's go to the hospital.

365
00:24:42,315 --> 00:24:44,971
Get me some water.

366
00:24:45,004 --> 00:24:46,004
Okay.

367
00:24:53,690 --> 00:24:54,829
Here. Drink this.

368
00:25:02,148 --> 00:25:03,671
Mom, we need to go to the hospital.

369
00:25:05,481 --> 00:25:07,996
Just let me catch my breath.

370
00:25:08,606 --> 00:25:10,186
Then we can go.

371
00:25:11,356 --> 00:25:13,022
You haven't eaten anything, right?

372
00:25:13,898 --> 00:25:15,488
I'll make you some porridge, Mom.

373
00:25:35,118 --> 00:25:36,853
What are we doing here?

374
00:25:36,856 --> 00:25:38,979
Let's just take a quick look.

375
00:25:38,981 --> 00:25:40,013
I feel uncomfortable.

376
00:25:40,023 --> 00:25:41,562
Why are you uncomfortable?

377
00:25:41,565 --> 00:25:42,951
It'll be our house soon.

378
00:25:45,418 --> 00:25:46,603
Earlier today,

379
00:25:46,606 --> 00:25:48,437
I checked the property records
because I was bored.

380
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:50,240
There really is something we can inherit.

381
00:25:50,940 --> 00:25:53,520
You checked what? Out of boredom?

382
00:25:53,523 --> 00:25:56,090
- Are you seriously doing this again?
- What's wrong with that?

383
00:25:56,523 --> 00:25:59,745
I already applied to a kindergarten
around here for O Reum.

384
00:25:59,773 --> 00:26:01,682
If O Reum gets in, let's move here.

385
00:26:02,044 --> 00:26:04,648
It's nice, and it's close
to my parents' place too.

386
00:26:04,902 --> 00:26:06,633
Enough. Come out.

387
00:26:07,112 --> 00:26:09,090
What's wrong with you? Let's go inside.

388
00:26:09,185 --> 00:26:11,748
- Just once. Why not?
- You'll wake O Reum.

389
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:14,158
- Seriously...
- Come out.

390
00:26:14,963 --> 00:26:17,815
- Come out right now.
- I told you, it'll be fine.

391
00:26:17,856 --> 00:26:18,945
O Reum will wake up.

392
00:26:18,948 --> 00:26:20,298
Just once.

393
00:26:31,705 --> 00:26:32,786
Hello.

394
00:26:33,690 --> 00:26:35,729
You don't look well.

395
00:26:35,731 --> 00:26:36,940
What's going on?

396
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,890
- Why are you here?
- No particular reason.

397
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:42,813
We came to see the house and look around.

398
00:26:42,815 --> 00:26:43,940
Our house?

399
00:26:43,949 --> 00:26:46,603
We're not making any decisions right now.

400
00:26:46,606 --> 00:26:49,220
We were just passing by,
and my parents live nearby...

401
00:26:49,223 --> 00:26:50,271
My goodness.

402
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:52,535
You two really went this far...

403
00:26:52,889 --> 00:26:54,583
This is really too much.

404
00:26:54,898 --> 00:26:59,188
My parents worked really hard
to buy this house.

405
00:26:59,190 --> 00:27:00,800
What gives you the right to do this?

406
00:27:01,065 --> 00:27:02,746
What do you mean, what right?

407
00:27:03,298 --> 00:27:08,070
The man who worked so hard
to buy it was my father-in-law too.

408
00:27:09,065 --> 00:27:13,356
- Are you two asking for a fight?
- Mom!

409
00:27:14,731 --> 00:27:18,065
Don't touch her.
I'm so disappointed in you.

410
00:27:18,148 --> 00:27:20,148
I never imagined you'd act like this.

411
00:27:21,648 --> 00:27:24,832
Mom, wake up!

412
00:27:25,231 --> 00:27:26,440
Mom!

413
00:27:52,356 --> 00:27:55,676
(Family Register)

414
00:27:55,773 --> 00:27:57,773
How can you say you have any right?

415
00:27:57,856 --> 00:27:59,273
We can't let them win.

416
00:27:59,315 --> 00:28:00,856
But we didn't do anything.

417
00:28:00,898 --> 00:28:03,940
The law doesn't protect homewreckers.

418
00:28:03,981 --> 00:28:05,356
You lied about the bullying, right?

419
00:28:05,359 --> 00:28:06,396
Because of your lie,

420
00:28:06,398 --> 00:28:07,813
she was eliminated from the contest.

421
00:28:07,815 --> 00:28:08,896
There are no secrets in this world.

422
00:28:08,898 --> 00:28:09,979
I'll find out the truth.

423
00:28:09,981 --> 00:28:11,731
Are you in love or something?
With that jerk who has no legs?

424
00:28:11,898 --> 00:28:14,063
You're dating a married woman.

425
00:28:14,065 --> 00:28:15,981
Let's teach that bastard a lesson.

426
00:28:18,110 --> 00:28:20,110
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
